This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of mixed-size training to improve the generalization and speed of CNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel training regime that involves mixing image sizes, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
